use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534009\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534009\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yay1665702959306.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yay1665702959306.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yay1665702959306.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yay1665702959306\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Using Oracle for the Repository\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Oracle can be used for the Uniface Repository.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yay1665702959306__p_d56342e1_d56343e1_d56344e1\">Consider the following when storing the Uniface Repository in Oracle:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25748e1_d25749e1_d25750e1\">The Uniface meta dictionary uses variable-length storage techniques with platform-specific data formats. To access the dictionary via SQL*Net, you must install Uniface with the <code class=\"ph codeph\">independent byte order</code> option set.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25751e1_d25752e1_d25753e1\">You can store the Repository in Oracle only when the default packing code mapping of the connector is used. However, you can set the following connector options before creating the Repository:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25754e1_d25755e1_d25756e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">disable segmented fields</code> can be set because there are no segmented fields in the dictionary. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ptz1665702732397.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ptz1665702732397.html\" title=\"Disable BLOB support. Map fields with segmented interface into the variable portion of the record.\">disable segmented fields</a>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25757e1_d25758e1_d25759e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">map fixed length to variable</code> can be set. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hoa1665702732769.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hoa1665702732769.html\" title=\"Map fields with a fixed length storage format (CHAR) to a variable length storage format.\">map fixed length to variable</a>.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25760e1_d25761e1_d25762e1\">Uniface assigns a special meaning to some characters in VARCHAR2, CHAR and LONG fields in the Repository. Uniface does not work correctly if these characters are corrupted when Oracle converts character data between character sets. To avoid this problem, define the Oracle client character set . You can do this by using the Oracle <code class=\"ph codeph\">NLS_LANG</code> environment variable.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25763e1_d25764e1_d25765e1\">To improve performance, it is recommended that (if your system setup can support it) you allow the ORA connector to open between 150 and 250 cursors when accessing the Repository in Oracle. The number you need depends on how extensively you use the features of the Uniface IDE. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aui1665702732980.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aui1665702732980.html\" title=\"Set maximum number of cursors per logon path which may be explicitly opened.\">open cursors</a>.\n                                <p class=\"p\" id=\"yay1665702959306__p_d56345e1_d56346e1_d56347e1\">When you test forms in Uniface, you may want to allow extra cursors for the tables accessed by those forms. This is only necessary if you access the test data on the same logon path as the Repository.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25766e1_d25767e1_d25768e1\">The connector option <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">disable cache</span> lowers the number of cursors the Uniface IDE keeps open (cursor attached to cached statement) in the application to a minimum. However, setting this will decrease the performance. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pmj1665702731884.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pmj1665702731884.html\" title=\"Keeps only the most recent statement in cache.\">disable cache</a>.\n                              </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yay1665702959306__li_d25769e1_d25770e1_d25771e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yay1665702959306__p_d56348e1_d56349e1_d56350e1\">You can use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">$E6_BASE_DATE</code> assignment setting to store 0-1-0000 for empty Time and DateTime fields. The format is as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[SETTINGS]\n$E6_BASE_DATE 0000\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yay1665702959306__p_d56351e1_d56352e1_d56353e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rtl1665702722696.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rtl1665702722696.html\" title=\"Store 0-1-000 for empty Time and DateTime fields.\">$E6_BASE_DATE</a>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534009\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534009\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Using Oracle for the Repository Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Using Oracle for the Repository Oracle can be used for the Uniface Repository. Consider the following when storing the Uniface Repository in Oracle: The Uniface meta dictionary uses variable-length storage techniques with platform-specific data formats. To access the dictionary via SQL*Net, you must install Uniface with the independent byte order option set. You can store the Repository in Oracle only when the default packing code mapping of the connector is used. However, you can set the following connector options before creating the Repository: disable segmented fields can be set because there are no segmented fields in the dictionary. For more information, see disable segmented fields . map fixed length to variable can be set. For more information, see map fixed length to variable . Uniface assigns a special meaning to some characters in VARCHAR2, CHAR and LONG fields in the Repository. Uniface does not work correctly if these characters are corrupted when Oracle converts character data between character sets. To avoid this problem, define the Oracle client character set . You can do this by using the Oracle NLS_LANG environment variable. To improve performance, it is recommended that (if your system setup can support it) you allow the ORA connector to open between 150 and 250 cursors when accessing the Repository in Oracle. The number you need depends on how extensively you use the features of the Uniface IDE. For more information, see open cursors . When you test forms in Uniface, you may want to allow extra cursors for the tables accessed by those forms. This is only necessary if you access the test data on the same logon path as the Repository. The connector option disable cache lowers the number of cursors the Uniface IDE keeps open (cursor attached to cached statement) in the application to a minimum. However, setting this will decrease the performance. For more information, see disable cache . You can use the $E6_BASE_DATE assignment setting to store 0-1-0000 for empty Time and DateTime fields. The format is as follows: [SETTINGS] $E6_BASE_DATE 0000 Copy For more information, see $E6_BASE_DATE Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}